32#ifndef _COMMON_H_INCLUDED
33#define _COMMON_H_INCLUDED
34
35#define FTP_DEFAULT_PORT 21
36#define HTTP_DEFAULT_PORT 80
37#define FTP_DEFAULT_PROXY_PORT 21
38#define HTTP_DEFAULT_PROXY_PORT 3128
39
40#ifdef WITH_SSL
41#include <openssl/crypto.h>
42#include <openssl/x509.h>
43#include <openssl/pem.h>
44#include <openssl/ssl.h>
45#include <openssl/err.h>
46#endif
47
48#if !defined(__sun) && !defined(__hpux) && !defined(__INTERIX) && \
49 !defined(__digital__) && !defined(__linux) && !defined(__MINT__) && \
50 !defined(__sgi)
51#define HAVE_SA_LEN
52#endif
53
54/* Connection */
55typedef struct fetchconn conn_t;
56
57struct fetchconn {
58 int sd; /* socket descriptor */
59 char *buf; /* buffer */
60 size_t bufsize; /* buffer size */
61 size_t buflen; /* length of buffer contents */
62 char *next_buf; /* pending buffer, e.g. after getln */
63 size_t next_len; /* size of pending buffer */
64 int err; /* last protocol reply code */
65#ifdef WITH_SSL
66 SSL *ssl; /* SSL handle */
67 SSL_CTX *ssl_ctx; /* SSL context */
68 X509 *ssl_cert; /* server certificate */
69# if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x00909000L
70 SSL_METHOD *ssl_meth; /* SSL method */
71# else
72 const SSL_METHOD *ssl_meth; /* SSL method */
73# endif
74#endif
75
76 char *ftp_home;
77
78 struct url *cache_url;
79 int cache_af;
80 int (*cache_close)(conn_t *);
81 conn_t *next_cached;
82};
83
84/* Structure used for error message lists */
85struct fetcherr {
86 const int num;
87 const int cat;
88 const char *string;
89};
90
91void fetch_seterr(struct fetcherr *, int);
92void fetch_syserr(void);
93void fetch_info(const char *, ...) __printflike(1, 2);
94int fetch_default_port(const char *);
95int fetch_default_proxy_port(const char *);
96int fetch_bind(int, int, const char *);
97conn_t *fetch_cache_get(const struct url *, int);
98void fetch_cache_put(conn_t *, int (*)(conn_t *));
99conn_t *fetch_connect(struct url *, int, int);
100conn_t *fetch_reopen(int);
101int fetch_ssl(conn_t *, int);
102ssize_t fetch_read(conn_t *, char *, size_t);
103int fetch_getln(conn_t *);
104ssize_t fetch_write(conn_t *, const void *, size_t);
105int fetch_close(conn_t *);
106int fetch_add_entry(struct url_list *, struct url *, const char *, int);
107int fetch_netrc_auth(struct url *url);
108int fetch_no_proxy_match(const char *);
109int fetch_urlpath_safe(char);
110
111#define ftp_seterr(n) fetch_seterr(ftp_errlist, n)
112#define http_seterr(n) fetch_seterr(http_errlist, n)
113#define netdb_seterr(n) fetch_seterr(netdb_errlist, n)
114#define url_seterr(n) fetch_seterr(url_errlist, n)
115
116fetchIO *fetchIO_unopen(void *, ssize_t (*)(void *, void *, size_t),
117 ssize_t (*)(void *, const void *, size_t), void (*)(void *));
118
119/*
120 * I don't really like exporting http_request() and ftp_request(),
121 * but the HTTP and FTP code occasionally needs to cross-call
122 * eachother, and this saves me from adding a lot of special-case code
123 * to handle those cases.
124 *
125 * Note that _*_request() free purl, which is way ugly but saves us a
126 * whole lot of trouble.
127 */
128fetchIO *http_request(struct url *, const char *,
129 struct url_stat *, struct url *, const char *);
130fetchIO *ftp_request(struct url *, const char *, const char *,
131 struct url_stat *, struct url *, const char *);
132

134/*
135 * Check whether a particular flag is set
136 */
137#define CHECK_FLAG(x) (flags && strchr(flags, (x)))
